Control System 
- Open loop == unadjusted distance on it's own (without feedback to adjust for output)

input ---> SYSTEM ---> output

- Feedback Control == allow system to make adjustements
--> Creates an Error=Delta from current position to GOAL to adjust new distance

PID --> We are removing error across time to even out to 0, Constant adjustment!! 

Proportional ==> multiplied by Kp

Integral ==> multiplied by Ki & integrated
--> takes constant/continueos erros 
===> Summation to find a value to adjust it by


Derivative ==> multiplied by Kd & differentiated
--> STEEPER ==> Faster error changes larger it becomes

Kp, Ki, Kd are called GAINS

